## Attribution Requirements

### 1. General Attribution
The above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all
copies or substantial portions of the Software.

### 2. Commercial Use Attribution
For any COMMERCIAL USE of this Software, the following attribution requirements
MUST be met:

a) **Visible Attribution**: Every user-facing page, interface, or output that
   utilizes this Software must display the following attribution in a clearly
   visible manner:
   
   "Powered by Email Pipeline by Alec Meeker and Applequist Inc."
   
   OR at minimum:
   
   "Powered by Applequist Inc."

b) **Attribution Specifications**:
   - The attribution must be legible and prominently displayed
   - For web applications: displayed on every page footer or header
   - For desktop applications: displayed in the main interface
   - For API services: included in API responses headers or documentation
   - For mobile applications: displayed on main screens and about sections
   - The attribution text must link to https://applequist.com when technically feasible

c) **Attribution Styling**:
   - Font size must be at least 10px or 0.625rem
   - Contrast ratio must meet WCAG 2.1 AA standards
   - Must not be hidden, obscured, or made less prominent through styling

### 3. Non-Commercial Use
For NON-COMMERCIAL USE (personal, educational, research, or non-profit use),
the general attribution requirement (Section 1) applies, but the visible
attribution requirement (Section 2) is optional though appreciated.

### 4. Source Code Distribution
Any distribution of source code must retain all copyright notices, this license
file, and attribution requirements intact.

## Commercial Use Definition

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software that:
- Generates revenue directly or indirectly
- Is used within a for-profit organization
- Provides services to paying customers
- Is incorporated into commercial products or services

